name: io.bytes.per.checksum
description:
The number of bytes per checksum.  Must not be larger than
  io.file.buffer.size.

name: dfs.client.hedged.read.threadpool.size
description:
Support 'hedged' reads in DFSClient. To enable this feature, set the parameter
    to a positive number. The threadpool size is how many threads to dedicate
    to the running of these 'hedged', concurrent reads in your client.

name: yarn.app.mapreduce.am.job.task.listener.thread-count
description:
The number of threads used to handle RPC calls in the
    MR AppMaster from remote tasks

name: mapreduce.reduce.shuffle.fetch.retry.timeout-ms
description:
Timeout value for fetcher to retry to fetch again when some
  non-fatal failure happens because of some events like NM restart.

name: dfs.namenode.top.num.users
description: Number of top users returned by the top tool

name: dfs.ha.fencing.ssh.connect-timeout
description:
SSH connection timeout, in milliseconds, to use with the builtin
    sshfence fencer.

name: yarn.app.mapreduce.am.job.committer.cancel-timeout
description:
The amount of time in milliseconds to wait for the output
    committer to cancel an operation if the job is killed
